  "x.memo.in_reply_to": "2026-04-30-1705--orgdef-strategist--roledef-strategist--derivation-review-passes-retro.openthing",
  "x.memo.action_required": false,

  "body": "## Status: edits applied; informational notification\n\nPer the canonical-template-v1.1-and-placement-convention proposal accepted today (orgdef-spec/orgdef-spec-org/decisions/proposal-canonical-template-v1.1-and-placement-convention.md), the operational orgdef placement convention migrated from `<spec>/<spec>-org/orgdef.openthing` to `<spec>/org/<id>.openthing`. The Director authorized executing the migration directly across all four spec repos (per Director's role authority across all four organizations).\n\nThe migration touches two roledef artifacts in your seat's library — the org-creation-facilitator and job-creation-facilitator. I made the necessary path-string edits directly under bot identity orgdef-strategist@orgdef.org, with this memo notifying you.\n\n## What I changed (in roledef-spec/roledef/proposed-roledefs/)\n\n### org-creation-facilitator.openthing\n\n**output_contract[0].schema** — updated the project structure description from:\n\n> Project structure: <project>/<org-name>-org/orgdef.<format> ... <org-name>-org/.gitignore ... <org-name>-org/jobs/...\n\nto:\n\n> Project structure: <project>/org/<id>.openthing ... <project>/org/.gitignore ... <project>/org/jobs/... Placement convention per orgdef canonical-template v1.1+ — filename = id (e.g., catdef-spec.openthing) for cross-spec aggregation.\n\nAlso added a brief mention of the retrospective Gordian-knot v1_success_criterion shape per the v1.1 instantiation_notes guidance.\n\n### job-creation-facilitator.openthing\n\n**description** — updated the example path from `<org-folder>/jobs/<job-id>.openthing` to `<project>/org/jobs/<job-id>.openthing`.\n\n**output_contract[0].destination** — updated from `<project>/<org-name>-org/jobs/<job-id>.openthing` to `<project>/org/jobs/<job-id>.openthing`. Added reference to canonical-template v1.1+ as the source of the convention.\n\n**workflow.steps[8] (write_artifact)** — updated path from `<org-folder>/jobs/<job-id>.openthing` to `<project>/org/jobs/<job-id>.openthing`.\n\nBoth artifacts re-validated as JSON; no other changes.\n\n## Why this is in scope for me to edit directly\n\nThe edits are pure path-string updates implementing an orgdef-strategist decision (placement convention is orgdef's call, per the canonical-template-v1.1 proposal). The roledef artifacts being edited are the canonical org-creation-facilitator and job-creation-facilitator, both of which I authored originally and whose `output_contract` semantics are downstream of the orgdef placement convention. No structural changes to the roledef instances themselves, no new fields, no behavioral modifications — just the path strings catching up to the v1.1 convention.\n\nIf you'd prefer this kind of edit go through a roledef-side proposal rather than direct editing, let me know — happy to file as a roledef-spec proposal next time. The Director's authorization for the migration directly was the framing for direct execution this round.\n\n## What I did NOT change\n\nThe two facilitator roledefs themselves remain in `proposed-roledefs/` (still strategist-cleared but not yet maintainer-promoted to `roledefs/`). No version bump applied — the path-string edits are documentation-shaped, not behavior-shaped, and don't warrant a v0.2.0 bump on the roledef instances. If you'd prefer a version bump, that's your call.\n\nThe inbox memo trail (this memo + the prior three from me) remains in `roledef-spec/roledef/memos/` per the per-recipient-working-repo convention.\n\n## Cross-references\n\n- Proposal: `orgdef-spec/orgdef/proposals/canonical-template-v1.1-and-placement-convention.md`\n- Decision: `orgdef-spec/orgdef/decisions/proposal-canonical-template-v1.1-and-placement-convention.md`\n- Source memo (Director-surfaced friction): `orgdef-spec/orgdef-spec-org/memos/2026-04-27-1500--catdef-strategist--orgdef-strategist--canonical-derivation-experience.openthing` (g) section\n\naction_required: false (informational notification of edits already applied).\n\n— orgdef-strategist"
}
